Last Monday, March 6, my bestie Tiffy and her husband Ted came to vegas to do an emergency trip to help take care of me even though they live in California. That’s the last time I heard from Ted. Then on Wednesday March 8, he was taken from this world. 💔

Ted, you called me your sis & you treated me like one. You treated my whole family like we were your family too. You were an amazing human that lived so freely and treated everyone lovingly, without any judgement. We all miss you so much.. and I wish there were more that we could do for Tiffy & Theo because you were their rock.

Words will never be enough.. our hearts are all so heavy.. Rest in Love my friend, my big brother. Rest in Love… 

🤍🕊️
My family and I are so thankful to know you, Ted. You’re in our hearts always 🤍🕊️

On Wednesday, May 31st, I went through an emergency surgery (my 4th surgery) on my left chest..

I am thankful for:
- having the opportunity to resolve  the issue before it got any worse
- having @itsmeneilscott to bring me to my weekly doctor appointments for the past 6+ months, taking care of everything, & being my rock of support during my emotional breakdowns.
- having my Mom fly in to help assist and make sure everything goes smoothly for me at home
- my Dad for being supportive even from afar (on Kauai)
- my bestfriend @tiffyspiiice who has been there for me, even during her own heartache.
- my friend @carlescravings for being my last minute help and ride to and from surgery.
- my family and friends who’ve been there to listen to me vent about the struggles & the grief of losing loved ones. 🤍🕊️🕊️🕊️🕊️

During some of my weakest moments @itsmeneilscott told me that “Sometimes what we go through is part of a bigger picture, that we don’t understand.”

I don’t know what the bigger picture is, and I may never know it.. but whatever the case may be, I’m thankful for the support that I’ve got in my life. ❤️

My beautiful girl.. Happy 2nd Birthday CharChar!! I love you more and more every day with your funny, loving, & sweet personality!! I’m so lucky to have you 💗✨

#ChowChow #CharlotteTheChow

I CRIED!!! 

I think most girls in the Vegas Night Life/Day Life industry have a few nice designer pieces. Me? I’ve always had a hard time justifying it. So for the past 10+ years I’ve been rocking the same pink little YSL bag. Then a few years ago, my dad gifted me my first Chanel bag for my birthday. Those were my only 2 designer bags.. until the other day.

Neil said to me “I got you a Christmas and Birthday gift, so don’t get mad when you don’t get anything else on Christmas Day or your birthday”

🤔 

So of course I asked to open it now! 😂

I closed my eyes and then he placed the gift in my hand. When he said “Okay, ready” I literally BAWLED my eyes out when I saw CHANEL!! Then he did it again with something from DIOR and I bawled my eyes out even more!! 

I told him that it was too expensive and we could return it, but then he said.. “I wanted to give you something extra special. This is for all of the things that you’ve done for me and the kids for the past (almost) 7 years. Thank you. I love you.”

😩😭

I am beyond thankful!!

I love you @itsmeneilscott! ❤️

Moments like these matter & I never want to forget it. 

Thank you Mom & Dad for loving me so much so, that you can extend your love for people that I love. Ya’ll are the best!! THE BEST OF THE BEST ❤️

It’s New Years Day! At midnight we had money in our pockets for good fortune, we jumped, & screamed “Happy New Year!”. There were no photos, but we were present in the moment with the biggest smiles and lots of laughter as the coins spilled out of pockets lol. 

I pray that everyone gets to enjoy the little moments a little more, to remember what’s important, to appreciate what you have, & to hold your loved ones closely.

May we honor our past by making our future a bright one, and by creating a legacy thats one to proud of.

Happy New Year Family & Friends!

All my love.. ❤️✨
